sentences.english: I don’t remember much of Thursday.
sentences.chinese: 那个周三的事我已经记得不大清楚了。

sentences.english: From the Macartney Mission to China, western world had begun to pay attention to "DA QING LU LI" or "Laws of Great Qing".
sentences.chinese: 西方社会关注《大清律例》始自马戛尔尼使团访华。

sentences.english: Gossip girl: I bet you’re wondering what gossip girl is doing up so early.
sentences.chinese: 我敢肯定你们都在疑惑绯闻少女大清早的在干吗。

sentences.english: I can’t remember all of them now, except for one.
sentences.chinese: 除了一个故事，其他的我现在都记不大清了。

sentences.english: Very early next morning Jaimie heard the noise again.
sentences.chinese: 接下来的早上，一大清早，杰米又听到了那个声音。

sentences.english: Hai Rui was an honest and upright official in the Ming Dynasty . He led a very simple life.
sentences.chinese: 海瑞斯明代的一个大清官，他生活也很简朴。

sentences.english: CENTURY ago it was the "national language" of a vast empire.
sentences.chinese: 一个世纪之前，满族语被定为大清王朝的“国语”。

sentences.english: Big Mosque on the main road of Omdurman.
sentences.chinese: 恩图曼干道上的大清真寺。

sentences.english: Muslim worshippers circle the Kaaba at Mecca's Grand Mosque during Ramadan.
sentences.chinese: 穆斯林朝圣者聚集在麦加的大清真寺周围。

sentences.english: Fans began lining up early in the morning to buy their cup - tie tickets.
sentences.chinese: 球迷大清早就开始排队，等着买优胜杯决赛的入场券。

sentences.english: Given the turnover of dynasties in the past, I don't think the Qing could be revived.
sentences.chinese: 过往朝廷覆辙在前，我想大清不还阳的那天了。

sentences.english: I don't know his name exactly.
sentences.chinese: 我已记不大清楚他的名字了。

sentences.english: Sorry, I can't hear you. Could you speak a little louder?
sentences.chinese: 对不起，我听不大清楚。您能再大声点吗？

sentences.english: Muslim worshippers circle the Kaaba at Mecca's Grand Mosque during Ramadan.
sentences.chinese: 斋月期间，聚集在麦加大清真寺外的穆斯林朝圣者。

sentences.english: He is eternally telephoning me early in the morning .
sentences.chinese: 他总是大清早给我打电话。

sentences.english: The great Qing Empire is done for.
